.TH ECHO 1 "2025" "Nightingale" "User Commands"
.SH NAME
echo \- display a line of text
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B echo
.RI [ STRING ]...
.SH DESCRIPTION
Echo the STRING(s) to standard output, separated by spaces and
followed by a newline.
.SH EXAMPLES
.TP
.B echo Hello World
Print "Hello World" followed by a newline.
.TP
.B echo "Hello   World"
Print with preserved spacing.
.TP
.B echo foo bar > file.txt
Redirect output to a file.
.SH NOTES
The Nightingale echo does not support:
.IP \(bu 3
.B \-n
option (suppress newline)
.IP \(bu
.B \-e
option (interpret escape sequences)
.IP \(bu
Backslash escape sequences
.SH SEE ALSO
.BR printf (3),
.BR puts (3)
